title: Obese_Serum_Subject 005-5
characteristics_ch1.5: sample type: FABP4+ (adipocyte-derived) exosomes isolated from serum
extract_protocol_ch1: To isolate exosomes, we used the serum from lean and obese subejcts and used ExoQuick-TC precipitation solution, according to ExoQuick-TC protocol. Total RNA was isolated following mirVana's total RNA Isolation kit. We also used StemCell Technologies Magnetic Isolation Technique to isolate FABP4+ specific exosomes.
label_protocol_ch1: We used Affymetrix FlashTag Biotin HSR RNA Labeling Kit to label 1000 ng of cRNA from each sample
hyb_protocol: For hybridization, we followed Affymetrix Gene Chip miRNA Array Procedure for Affymetrix miRNA 4.0 arrays to hybridize biotin-labeled sample
scan_protocol: We scanned the Affymetrix miRNA 4.0 arrays following the Affymetrix Command Console User Manual Instructions.
description: microRNA profiles of adipocyte-derived (FABP4+) exosomes isolated in subject serum
data_processing: We analyzed the resulting data in Expression Console using RMA+DMBG (Affymetrix) and then exported it to Partek Genomics Suite for analyses
